1. lifecycle methods can be added to our class based components but not to our stateless functional components

2.componentDidMount()
    a.componentDidMount() fires when the component first gets mounted to the dom

3.componentDidUpdate()
   a. componentDidUpdate() is going to fire after the component updates
   b. it is really useful when it comes to fiuring out exactly when your components data has changed

4. componentWillUnmount()
    a. componentWillUnmount() fires just before component goes away